# names.txt — Name anonymization mappings for anonymize.py
#
# Copy this file to names.txt and replace with your own mappings.
# names.txt is git-ignored and stays on your machine.
#
# Format: RealName → Label
# - One mapping per line
# - Lines starting with # are comments
# - Blank lines are ignored
# - Replacement is case-insensitive
# - Longer names are replaced before shorter ones automatically
#   (so "Anna" won't corrupt "Annabelle" if both are listed)
#
# Tips:
# - List full names AND first names separately if you use both
# - Include nicknames and common variations
# - Include relationship labels if you use them (e.g. "Dr. Smith → Doctor-A")

# --- People ---
John Smith → Person-A
John → Person-A
Sarah → Person-B
Dr. Chen → Doctor-A
Mom → Family-A
Dad → Family-B

# --- Places (optional) ---
# San Francisco → City-A
# New York → City-B

# --- Organizations (optional) ---
# Acme Corp → Company-A
